parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door latch sensor can cause the door to become impossible to open, posing a safety risk in emergency situations.
symptoms: The door cannot be opened
the door latch sensor is defective
the computer sensor in the door handle is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose vital information, such as speed, fuel level, and engine temperature, which can lead to accidents or unsafe driving conditions.
symptoms: The instrument cluster display is faded or illegible
the fuel gauge is inaccurate
the temperature gauge is faulty
the speedometer and tachometer function sporadically
the battery goes dead while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the direct ignition coil can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to unsafe driving conditions.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start
especially in cold weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front axle can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The axle falls out of the drive system
the vehicle makes a clunking or rattling noise
the vehicle is difficult to shift into gear
the vehicle is thrown into a spin.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission freezes up
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the vehicle makes a clunking or rattling noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drive train can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a clunking or rattling noise
the vehicle is difficult to shift into gear
the vehicle is thrown into a spin
the vehicle loses power or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight to turn on can reduce visibility, especially at night or in low-light conditions, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The headlight occasionally won't turn on
requires switching on/off multiple times to function
tends to happen more when the vehicle is cold.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the center console LED lights can lead to a lack of awareness of critical vehicle warnings, such as overheating or low oil levels, which can result in engine damage or accidents.
symptoms: The LED lights in the center console are going out
despite previous repairs
making it difficult to monitor vehicle warnings.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Xenon Headlight Light Mask Design Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the xenon headlight light masks can cause blind spots on the sides of the road, especially on rural roads without streetlights, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The xenon headlights make the sides of the road completely dark when turning more than 90 degrees
making it difficult for the driver to see the roadway.
